												</tr>
												<tr>
													<td class="textNormal" style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 13px; FONT-FAMILY: tahoma">Current 
														Approach
													</td>
												</tr>
												<tr>
													<td>
														<p class="textNormal">
															In the next phase of NAC, NASSCOM has been conducting NAC with different State 
															Governments, identified deemed Universities / Colleges in various states, etc. 
															The target audience is final-year students (from all ‘general’ streams) who 
															will be venturing into the job market after few months. The intent behind 
															assessing these students is to analyze the level of talent which is available 
															in various parts of country, especially in tier-2 and tier-3 cities. Gauging 
															this would eventually help identify regions in India where the readily 
															available BPO-fit talent exists; also identify the community that requires 
															training before joining the industry. These test takers are further provided an 
															opportunity to connect to various companies where they can showcase their NAC 
															scores which obviously helps a company identify the potential candidate.</p>
													</td>
												</tr>
